Tick-server is an Mochiweb based web server for epolling (streaming, long pooling, web sockets) 
testing purposes.

It starts send time ticks (unix epoch) 1 per sec, to any open connection 
as chunked HTTP/1.1 responses.

Using:

curl -v -s http://localhost:8383/tick/

> GET /tick/ HTTP/1.1
> User-Agent: curl/7.21.6 (x86_64-pc-linux-gnu) libcurl/7.21.6 OpenSSL/1.0.0e zlib/1.2.3.4 libidn/1.22 librtmp/2.3
> Host: localhost:8383
> Accept: */*
> 
< HTTP/1.1 200 OK
< Transfer-Encoding: chunked
< Server: Tick server
< Date: Wed, 04 Apr 2012 09:43:29 GMT
< Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8
< 
Tick server v.0.1 for 
1333532610 1
1333532611 2
1333532612 3
1333532613 4
.....
....


or try it with your client or browser with long polling support (Firefox, Chrome).
